âœ… Basic steps to create a custom REST API endpoint

1ï¸âƒ£ Register your custom endpoint using register_rest_route.
2ï¸âƒ£ Write a callback function to handle the request.
3ï¸âƒ£ Call it via HTTP (GET or POST).

ðŸ“Œ Example: Create GET /wp-json/custom/v1/hello
     ðŸ‘‰ Add this to your functions.php or a custom plugin:
       
add_action('rest_api_init', function () {
    register_rest_route('custom/v1', '/hello', array(
        'methods'  => 'GET',
        'callback' => 'custom_hello_endpoint',
    ));
});

function custom_hello_endpoint($request) {
    return rest_ensure_response(array(
        'message' => 'Hello Ruchi! This is your custom API.',
        'time' => current_time('mysql'),
    ));
}


  

